{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e8f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"414"},"text":"§ 414.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Insured status for purposes of old-age and survivors insurance benefits","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For the purposes of this subchapter—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e90-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" “Fully insured individual” defined","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “fully insured individual” means any individual who had not less than—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e91-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" one quarter of coverage (whenever acquired) for each calendar year elapsing after 1950 (or, if later, the year in which he attained age 21) and before the year in which he died or (if earlier) the year in which he attained age 62, except that in no case shall an individual be a fully insured individual unless he has at least 6 quarters of coverage; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e92-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 40 quarters of coverage; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e93-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of an individual who died before 1951, 6 quarters of coverage;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"not counting as an elapsed year for purposes of paragraph (1) any year any part of which was included in a period of disability (as defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s416/i"},"text":"section 416(i) of this title","children":[],"tail":"), and who satisfies the criterion specified in subsection (c)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e94-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" “Currently insured individual” defined","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “currently insured individual” means any individual who had not less than six quarters of coverage during the thirteen-quarter period ending with (1) the quarter in which he died, (2) the quarter in which he became entitled to old-age insurance benefits, (3) the quarter in which he became entitled to primary insurance benefits under this subchapter as in effect prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-08-28"},"text":"August 28, 1950","children":[],"tail":", or (4) in the case of any individual entitled to disability insurance benefits, the quarter in which he most recently became entitled to disability insurance benefits, not counting as part of such thirteen-quarter period any quarter any part of which was included in a period of disability unless such quarter was a quarter of coverage, and who satisfies the criterion specified in subsection (c)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e95-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Criterion described","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of subsections (a) and (b), the criterion specified in this subsection is that the individual, if not a United States citizen or national—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e96-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has been assigned a social security account number that was, at the time of assignment, or at any later time, consistent with the requirements of subclause (I) or (III) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s405/c/2/B/i"},"text":"section 405(c)(2)(B)(i) of this title","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e97-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" at the time any such quarters of coverage are earned—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e98-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/c/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is described in subparagraph (B) or (D) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t8/s1101/a/15"},"text":"section 1101(a)(15) of title 8","children":[],"tail":","}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e99-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/c/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is lawfully admitted temporarily to the United States for business (in the case of an individual described in such subparagraph (B)) or the performance as a crewman (in the case of an individual described in such subparagraph (D)), and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e9a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s414/c/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the business engaged in or service as a crewman performed is within the scope of the terms of such individual’s admission to the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb7424e9b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 214, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-08-28/ch809"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1950, ch. 809","children":[],"tail":", title I, § 104(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/492"},"text":"64 Stat. 492","children":[],"tail":", 505; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-07-18/ch945/s3/b"},"text":"July 18, 1952, ch. 945, § 3(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/770"},"text":"66 Stat. 770","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-09-01/ch1206"},"text":"Sept. 1, 1954, ch. 1206","children":[],"tail":", title I, §§ 106(b), 108(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/1079"},"text":"68 Stat. 1079","children":[],"tail":", 1083; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-01/ch836"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1956, ch. 836","children":[],"tail":", title I, § 108, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70/830"},"text":"70 Stat. 830","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/840/tII/s205"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–840, title II, § 205","children":[],"tail":"("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-08-28"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1025"},"text":"72 Stat. 1025","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/778/tII/s204/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–778, title II, § 204(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1960","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/74/948"},"text":"74 Stat. 948","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/64/tI/s103/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–64, title I, § 103(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/137"},"text":"75 Stat. 137","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/603/tI/s104/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–603, title I, § 104(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/1340"},"text":"86 Stat. 1340","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/203/tII/s211/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–203, title II, § 211(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-03-02"},"text":"Mar. 2, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/518"},"text":"118 Stat. 518","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb7424e9c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb7424e9d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idb7424e9e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/203/s211/a"},"text":"Section 211(a) of Pub. L. 108–203","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of section 214, was executed to this section, which is section 214 of the Social Security Act, to reflect the probable intent of Congress. See 2004 Amendment notes below."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb7424e9f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/203/s211/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–203, § 211(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, and who satisfies the criterion specified in subsection (c)” before period at end. See Codification note above."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/203/s211/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–203, § 211(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, and who satisfies the criterion specified in subsection (c)” before period at end. See Codification note above."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/203/s211/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–203, § 211(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c). See Codification note above."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1972—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/603"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–603","children":[],"tail":" struck out provisions setting a separate age computation point for women and reduced from age 65 to age 62 the age computation point for men."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1961—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/64"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–64","children":[],"tail":" required one quarter of coverage for each calendar year elapsing after 1950 (or after the year in which the individual attained age 21, if that was later than 1950) instead of one quarter of coverage for each three of the quarters elapsing after 1950, and struck out “unless such quarter was a quarter of coverage” after “a period of disability (as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s416/i"},"text":"section 416(i) of this title","children":[],"tail":")”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1960—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/778"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–778","children":[],"tail":" changed provisions which required an individual to have one quarter of coverage for each two quarters to provide that an individual is fully insured if he has not less than one quarter of coverage for each three quarters elapsing after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1950","children":[],"tail":", or, if later, December 31 of the year in which he attained the age of 21 years, and inserted provisions defining fully insured in the case of an individual who died prior to 1951 as one who had six quarters of coverage."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1958—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/840"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–840","children":[],"tail":" included within definition of “currently insured individual” an individual entitled to disability insurance benefits who has not less than six quarters of coverage during the thirteen-quarter period ending with the quarter in which he most recently became entitled to disability insurance benefits."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1956—Subsec. (a)(3). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-08-01"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1956","children":[],"tail":", provided that an individual who had at least six quarters of coverage after 1954 would be fully insured if all but four of the quarters elapsing after 1954 and prior to "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1957-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1957","children":[],"tail":", or if later, the quarter in which he attained retirement age or died, whichever first occurred, are quarters of coverage."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1954—Subsec. (a)(2)(B). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-09-01"},"text":"Sept. 1, 1954","children":[],"tail":", § 106(b)(1), excluded from the elapsed period under subsec. (a)(2)(A) any quarter any part of which was included in a period of disability, unless such quarter was a quarter of coverage."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(3), (4). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-09-01"},"text":"Sept. 1, 1954","children":[],"tail":", § 108(a), added par. (3) and redesignated former par. (3) as (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-09-01"},"text":"Sept. 1, 1954","children":[],"tail":", § 106(b)(2), inserted “, not counting as part of such thirteen-quarter period any quarter any part of which was included in a period of disability unless such quarter was a quarter of coverage.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1952—Subsec. (a)(2)(B). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1952-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1952","children":[],"tail":", § 3(b)(1), inserted “not counting as an elapsed quarter for purposes of subparagraph (A) any quarter any part of which was included in a period of disability (as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s416/i"},"text":"section 416(i) of this title","children":[],"tail":" unless such quarter was a quarter of coverage”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1952-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1952","children":[],"tail":", § 3(b)(2), inserted “not counting as part of such thirteen-quarter period any quarter any part of which was included in a period of disability unless such quarter was a quarter of coverage” after “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-08-28"},"text":"August 28, 1950","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb7424ea0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb7424ea1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2004 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/203/tII/s211/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–203, title II, § 211(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-03-02"},"text":"Mar. 2, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/518"},"text":"118 Stat. 518","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/108/203/tII/s211/c"},"text":"“The amendments made by this section [amending this section and ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s423"},"text":"section 423 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] apply to benefit applications based on social security account numbers issued on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2004","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb7424ea2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1972 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/603/tI/s104/j"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–603, title I, § 104(j)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/1341"},"text":"86 Stat. 1341","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/92/603/tI/s104/j"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The amendments made by this section [amending this section and sections 415, 416, 423, and 427 of this title and provisions set out as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s415"},"text":"section 415 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] (except the amendment made by subsection (i) [amending "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s3121"},"text":"section 3121 of Title 26","children":[],"tail":", Internal Revenue Code], and the amendment made by subsection (g) to section 209(i) of the Social Security Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s409/i"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 409(i)","children":[],"tail":"]) shall apply only in the case of a man who attains (or would attain) age 62 after December 1974. The amendment made by subsection (i), and the amendment made by subsection (g) to section 209(i) of the Social Security Act, shall apply only with respect to payments after 1974."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In the case of a man who attains age 62 prior to 1975, the number of his elapsed years for purposes of section 215(b)(3) of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s415/b/3"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 415(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":"] shall be equal to (A) the number determined under such section as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-09-01"},"text":"September 1, 1972","children":[],"tail":", or (B) if less, the number determined as though he attained age 65 in 1975, except that monthly benefits under title II of the Social Security Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s401"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 401","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] for months prior to January 1973 payable on the basis of his wages and self-employment income shall be determined as though this section had not been enacted."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In the case of a man who attains or will attain age 62 in 1973, the figure ‘65’ in sections 214(a)(1), 223(c)(1)(A), and 216(i)(3)(A) of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s414/a/1"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 414(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", 423(c)(1)(A), 416(i)(3)(A)] shall be deemed to read ‘64’."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In the case of a man who attains or will attain age 62 in 1974, the figure ‘65’ in sections 214(a)(1), 223(c)(1)(A), and 216(i)(3)(A) of the Social Security Act shall be deemed to read ‘63’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb7424ea3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1961 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/64/tI/s103/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–64, title I, § 103(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/137"},"text":"75 Stat. 137","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/87/64/tI/s103/b"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"“The amendment made by subsection (a) [amending this section] shall apply—","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of monthly benefits under title II of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s401"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 401","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] for months beginning on or after the effective date of this title [see note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s402"},"text":"section 402 of this title","children":[],"tail":"], based on applications filed in or after March 1961,"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of lump-sum death payments under such title with respect to deaths on or after the effective date of this title, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attr